    "abstract": "This Research Note reads Stephen Wolfram's 2026 ruliological P-vs-NP essay as an external comparator for a bounded Panta Rhei question: when does witness search become finite address construction? It keeps Wolfram's finite ruliological microcosms, the internal tau-admissibility claim, and orthodox Clay/Turing/ZFC P vs NP strictly separated.",
    "claim_boundary": {
      "claim": "Under finite interface width and a reconstruction discipline, some tau-admissible witness problems can be treated as address construction rather than blind witness search.",
      "non_claim": "It does not solve orthodox P vs NP, identify the Ruliad with Category tau, or claim Wolfram validates Panta Rhei."
